DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text: What happened that day, many years ago?

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text: I fucked up.

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text: She was an asshole.

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text: And there's nothing more to it than that. I'm overthinking.

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text: I ran away, just like that.

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text: I thought the most popular girl in class would miraculously like me.

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text: And she %broke me%.

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text: Klara er bekymret om hvad der vil ske. Begynder at tænke over hvordan hun går til det, hvad Sofie vil tænke, og hvordan hun "vinder Sofie over"

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text: She was only messing with me. I acted smartly.

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text: Did I hurt her? Would she ever be hurt by someone like me?

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text: ... maybe she did?

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text: ... and she crushed that dream with a hammer.

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text: Calling it "overthinking" is just an excuse to be lazy.

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text: She was an asshole, but...

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text: I already %was% broke.

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text: I've been broke ever since.

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text: Oh to hell with it, not again!

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text: I can't %think% my way to this conclusion, I should know that already... I'm here today because i need to confront her %head-on%.

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text: I mean, there's a reason I decided to do this today, of all days. She's gonna think I'm here for the bus to the reunion, not for her specifically.

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text: She's gonna be surprised I'm actually going to that shitshow. She's gonna think 'wow, can you take a hint? You weren't %really% supposed to come today ...' and find some excuse to make fun of me, but not really, just %implied%, just enough to hurt but not enough for me to do or say anything about it. She's gonna be on top, her perfect comfort-zone.

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text: Then ... BAM! That's when I strike! That's when I tell her what I thought about her all those years ... what I've thought about her since ...  what she's done to me ... !

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text: She has a strong tendency to completely control the situation, so I just need to be straight. I'll never beat her in wits or smarts, she'll circle around me. I'll never seem superior, she always has a way to come out on top. The only thing I can hope to do is make her feel something.

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text: She has a thousand ways of dealing with insults, but a genuine emotional confession would scare her. When sarcasm and wit is inappropriate, she is suddenly ripped of all her weapons and shields.

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text: I just need to be honest about my feelings. Gut-wrenchingly honest.

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Narrator
DialogueFragments.Text: The girl to the right runs over to the approaching girl and gives her a big hug.

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Narrator
DialogueFragments.Text: The girl to the left, however, is baffled. After a little while, they ease out slightly from the hug.

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: [X]"I'm so happy to see you!"

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: "You're going to the reunion party too?"

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: "I didn't expect to see you here!"

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text: "Me neither."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text: "Mhm".

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text: "I am."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: "Well that's great!"

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: "I am too!"

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text: "Haha"

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: "Anyways, you look ... tense. Sit down!"

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text: "Are you surprised I'm going to the party?"

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text: "I didn't wanna say no to your invitation".

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: "You didn't wanna say yes either, haha!"

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: "Of course not!"

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: "Well, I'm pleasantly surprised".

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text: "Oh uh ... yeah".

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text: "Oh, I mean, I had less than two weeks. Wasn't the event planned way before that?   ".

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: "Sorry."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: "I didn't wanna invite you initially because I was scared you would interpret it as some sick joke and distance yourself further."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text: "Fortunately for you, I don't understand sarcasm, so here I am!"

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text: "I always appreciate being invited."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: "Awwww."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: "That's the most brilliant thing i remember about you!"

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text: " ... you know, it's nice to see that things haven't changed too much since then. It's calming, in a way".

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text: "I remember that brilliant mouth of yours as well. Seemed like you could talk your way out of any situation."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: "Always so philosophical back then too!"

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text: "You're smart enough to know what I mean."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: "Thank you!"

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: "But alas, I could never get the same grades as someone real smart like you."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text: "Yeah, I just love philosophy."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: "Please explain it to me."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: "I never said I couldn't understand it, silly you!"

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text: "[X]Oh could you please, for just one second, stop pretending?"

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Narrator
DialogueFragments.Text: The girl coming in from the left is nearing the stop now.

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Narrator
DialogueFragments.Text: The girl coming in from the left is at the stop now. The girl to the right has noticed her now,

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: "You don't seem so excited! Are you trying to convince me you`re not excited to see classmates you haven't seen for 5 years that we're never even nice to you back then?"

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text: "Cool."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text: "Yeah."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: "You didn't expect to see you here either?"

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: "You didn't think i would come?"

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text: "Maybe."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text: "Didn't know if it was worth your time."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: "if I get to see you, then it was."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text: "It made me really happy when I saw it."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text: "Had almost a whole two weeks to do it, even. An event like this is usually planed a lot earlier, isn't it?"

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: "Seriously, you don't though".

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text: "And I never will!"

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text: "Everything could be sarcastic."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: "You just need perspective."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text: "But mine is all messed-up."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text: "And where would I find that?"

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: "That's a big question."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: "You just need to stop being so pessimistic."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: "I wanted you to come to this party. Full stop. It was not sarcastic, and I am not being sarcastic right now."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: "Of course not!"

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text: "Why?"

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: "It didn't really seem like your kind of thing."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: "You never replied when I invited you to the party, personally."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text: "I got really happy when i saw your invitation."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text: "No one is to blame. I never understand these kind of things anyways."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text: "I do."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: "It's the thought that counts."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: "Yeah, you we're always the smart kid in class back then."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: "It's a little difficult for me."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: "Awwww."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text: "And i never will!"

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: "Why would you think that?"

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text: "I don't know?"

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text: "... yeah."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: "I guess popularity comes at a price."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text: "... Yeah, maybe the jerks of the world all have good intentions, they just can't help but act like jerks in practice."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text: Say nothing.

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: "Sounds like a pain."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: [X]"... so, you doing well recently?"

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: "Awwww."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: "Don't start something like that".

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text: "Pretending that everything is fine. We're %best buds%, the two us. Just hanging out, having a good time!"

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text: "You think it's all just gonna go away if you ignore it long enough?"

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: "I don't like to dwell."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: "You're gonna need to be more concrete with me."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text: "Stop! I'm not trying to insult you."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text: "And it is for that same reason I want this over with."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text: "I forgive you. Wholeheartedly I feel no anger in my heart towards you."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: "Haha"

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: "I forgive you too!"

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text: "You were an asshole to me for years. I was the butt of your joke every time you needed to feel powerful in front of others."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text: "But it's okay. I forgive you, because I know you didn't mean to. We were rarely alone together, but in those sparse times, you we're always so nice to me. I forgive you because I know you had your own problems and you never truly wanted to hurt me."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: "We we're young and stupid back then."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: "Right, I am just compelled to be evil against my will, I can't control it, it's such a pain."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text: "I forgave you back then too, because at the graduation party when those girls were asking me to go home, you pulled my hand tight and asked them to eat shit. Your best friends."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: "And the lord praised my heroic deeds."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: "Alcohol does weird things to teenagers."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text: "I had never seen such determination and strength within you. It was beautiful. You were absolutely beautiful."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text: "I %had% to do something, so at the last day of school, I showed you my love like I showed it to the world. I opened up and spilled my guts for you. I was naked."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text: "And you stood quiet, you looked at me, you paused ... "

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text: "... and you laughed. It wasn't condescending, but it was true. And then you walked away and I haven't seen you since."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: "Listen ... "

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: "I never forbade you from seeing me."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text: "You didn't. And It's not your fault."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text: "You don't need to say sorry."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text: "Because I forgive you. Even after all these years, I'm drawn to you. I want to know you better, I want to be friends with you and I want to be able to love you."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text: "Please."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: "Oh quit with this drama!"

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: "This is just stupid. What do you even want me to say here?"

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: "Sorry!"

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: "It was me! Hoopti-doo, i fucked up!"

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: "I don't know, okay!"

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: "Or something ... "

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: "We can't, like, change the past."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: "It's just a big backhanded compliment, that's all it is."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: "I loved your analysis and prose, it was beautiful, very poetic!"

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: "You can't hurt me, no matter how hard you try!"

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: "It's not that complicated."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: "You we're awkward and I was an asshole, and then time moved on!"

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: "You just want it to be complicated because the truth is too harsh."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: "Actually ... I think you're telling me only half the truth."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: "I'm sorry. I am and I keep being it because at the end of the day the only thing I know how to be is an asshole."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: "Because when I don't, people run away in fear. I take their hand, and they think I'm gonna rip it off."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text: "I felt cornered and scared."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text: "Did you think things would change so easily?"

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: " ... you're talking nonsense here ... "

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: " ... I mean, thanks, but ... "

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: " ... i don't know what you want out of this, and ... "

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: " ... nothing good is gonna come out of this and ...  "

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: "I think you're a massive hypocrite."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: "Truth is, I'm leagues above you. I would never and will never feel validated by anything you do or say".

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text:
Hug her:
"But that's okay. That doesn't mean you're a bad person. It's just fate".

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: "You're just playing the biggest backhanded compliment of the century."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text: "I'm not trying to prove anything, I mean it."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text: "I want to love you but then you say things like this."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: "No? You're %above% superiority as a concept, of course; You just wanted to let me know how you've been doing! You've just found the good within yourself to forgive me, and you wanted to let me know, for my sake."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: "You are here to %help me% get through these tough times, to let me know that, actually, I'm not an asshole because I truly want to be, I am because I just can't help it!"

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: "Oh yeah, because you're doing this for %me% of course. Oh such relief! I'm so glad i can finally relax knowing I have your forgiveness, it's been driving me crazy this whole time!"

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text: "You're taking what I say out of context, that's clearly not what I meant."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text: "I'm trying to show you how good I truly think you could be."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: "I'm sorry. I am and I keep being it because at the end of the day the only thing I know how to be is an asshole."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: "Because when I don't, people run away in fear. I take their hand, and they think I'm gonna rip it off."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text: "I felt cornered and scared."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text: "Did you think things would change so easily?"

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: "And why is it so important for you that I know this? It is maybe because ... "

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: "And you're taking the whole situation out of context by omitting information."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: "When I'm not an asshole, when I somehow find it within myself to take %someone's% hand and help, they think I'm gonna rip it off and they run away in fear."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text: "I felt cornered and scared."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text: "Did you think you could change everything just like that?"

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: "Did and/or do you? It's fine to be an emotionless stone plate for years, just make up for it in the end, at the absolute last moment possible!"

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: "But you %always% did!"

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: "I don't think I could think of anyone who's harder to love than you. You make people feel like they're wolves trapped with a rabbit, anything they do is just bound to make you scared."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: "I was an asshole, but I %tried%, and you show your gratitude on the very last day of school before you run off and never contact me again."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: "Don't twist our time together into 'those sparse moments we we're alone'. We spent so much time, and I knew you were the smartest, kindest girl in class."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text: "You make people feel like they're trapped with a wolf."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text: "Should I not be afraid of my best friend who stabs me in the back every week?"

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: "Alas, your true nature is revealed: You are here to insult me and indulge in the sick, sweet catharsis of revenge. If you wanna reduce our relationship to this, go ahead."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: "I'll gladly help: "

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: "You stutter over your words because you're so nervous all the time, and it makes everyone else nervous all the same."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: "You're terrible at coming up with conversation so everyone else has to take the initiative for you."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: "You don't lighten up anyone's mood because you're just so sad. Or maybe you want to, but you're just too burdened by your absolute lack of any social skills to really give a solid try."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: "You never ask how people are doing, but expect them to do same. You don't talk to people, you talk %at% people. You have mastered the monologue but never bothered reading the lines."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: "You never show me empathy and think I care about your forgiveness. *I am leagues above you*. I will never feel validated by anything you do or say. You can never make me happy just as you never could back then."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text: "I'm not hurt."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text: "I've heard so much shit from you throughout the years that none of it feels significant. Give it some hours and you'll do a complete 180"

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text: "I've thought those things myself already a thousand times!"

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text: "Even though you couldn't be more different from me, you hate yourself just as much!"

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text: "Because like so many other things, you don't really care."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text: "You hate how utterly fucking uninteresting you are."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text: "You are scared by me!"

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text: She hates how utterly fucking uninteresting she is.

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text: Hates her lack of skills, lack of interests, lack of opinions, lack of any idea of what to do with her life.

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text: "You hate your lack of skills, lack of interests, lack of opinions, lack of any idea of what to do with your life."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text: "You need your companions of equally uninteresting people, just to feel okay."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text: "You we're the most popular girl in school, but you knew it really didn't mean anything."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text: "I am everything that you are not, because I know how to be alone."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text: "It makes sense that i can't validate you, because the only way you feel validated is to put people below you."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text: "Anyone else would be so happy to be in that position, but for you, it just felt empty."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text: "Then eventually, you leave them behind and find a pair of new ones."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Narrator
DialogueFragments.Text: At this point, the bus might honestly have gone past and they wouldn't have noticed a thing.

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Narrator
DialogueFragments.Text: They are staring intensely at each other, or, scratch that, they are staring intensely slightly past each other.

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: "Sorry, I wasn't really listening. Can I tell you a story?"

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text: "Okay."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: "My mother always told me when I was a kid".

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: "There's this island. It's far away a different time and place. People live on it, and they're very happy".

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: "Then one day, a mysterious-looking mask drifts ashore."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: "It's a nice piece of craftmanship for sure, but people don't think much of it. They already have a lot of masks, you see. It's passed around, used for play, decoration, various things, and eventually, it ends up right back on the beach, covered in sand".

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: "Months pass, and it's summer now. Every time this part of the year, they have a big party on the beach to celebrate the sun. Someone walks away from the crowd to take a quick leak, and then, the weirdest thing happens: "

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: "The masks insults her! It makes fun of her, it bullies her. This mask is verbose, it is articulate: It knows everything it needs to exploit her insecurities and crush her self-esteem completely".

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: "And yet ... "

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: "She becomes completely %transfixed% by it. So does the rest of the island, actually. The mask has become a phenomenon".

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: "It only insults people. It does nothing useful. They build a throne for it, and people come to get insulted, torn apart".

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: "The mask seems so smart. It knowns things about you that you didn't even know yourself!"

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: "And just imagine if the mask %didn't% insult you. You would be a truly, truly remarkable person, and you would know this with absolute certainty".

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: ".... The chieftain eventually leaves his throne to see what the fuss is all about. People are becoming distracted! They care more about following the mask than following *his orders*! As usual, it insults him. It insults him more throughly and for longer than it has ever insulted anyone else before".

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: "Everyone is watching in complete awe and quiet. After a long pause, the chieftain proclaims, quietly: `You cannot give the death penalty to a mask`. He then orders everyone to leave."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: "A few days later, the mask is found at the same place it stranded on the beach, burned to a heavy stone, looking forever at it's own reflection in the water"

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: "Insulting itself day in, day out".

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text: [X]"That's a fucked up children's story."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: "Haha."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text: [X]"Did you make this story up yourself?"

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text: [X]"I assume you're the mask in this story, correct?"

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: "I changed a couple of things."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: "I don't remember it very well, at least."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: "I hope not."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text: [X]"Why are you telling me this story?"

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: "Aren't we all? Or something like that?"

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text: "Like what?"

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text: "Hmm."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: "Don't think the mask was punished like that in the end, but who knows, my mom might not have told me the original."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text: "I guess I feel kind of like the mask, minus the part where people admire me."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: "Sounds shitty."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text: "Yeah."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: "Insulting is bad."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text:
"I felt like changing topic."
[D]"I felt rather hopeless."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text: "Yeah, it wasn't the best of moods I'll admit."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text: "Probably for the best."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: "We were throwing a lot of shit."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text: "I actually really enjoyed the story."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: "Thanks."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: "Why?"

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: "This thing actually made sense to you?"

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: "You we're always into the weird and grotesque."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text: "It's dark, it's brutal, it doesn't hold back to make us feel better. It dares to show us the truth, even if that truth sucks"

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: "Hope is such an overrated concept."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text: "It really is. I'm tired of being told to be optimistic when it just doesn't fit my reality."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: "Amen."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text: "Life sucks, am I right?"

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: "Amen amen."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: "Haha."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text: "Somehow, it just made me feel comfy."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text: "Can't see why it shouldn't. It's made for kids."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text: "It was nice hearing it from you."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: "Same."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: "Thanks."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: "What do you mean?"

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text: "It just seemed very genuine coming from you."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text: "When everything doesn't turn out well, maybe you're not doing anything wrong."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text: "Must have messed you up real bad as a kid."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: "Haha."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: "Or maybe you're doing everything wrong!"

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text: "Haha"

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: "Why did you enjoy the story?"

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: "The story actually made sense to you?"

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text: "Yeah. Insulting people is bad!"

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: "Haha, no, but really?"

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: "So what are they supposed to learn?"

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text: "I don't know. Assholes are empty husks on the inside that get it worse than death?"

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: "Haha."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text: "No. It's quite good actually."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: "Pinocchio must have had it hard you know. He's the only wooden boy in the world, no one could possibly understand his situation."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text: "Pinocchio's fucked up."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: "It's crazy."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text: "You ever feel like Pinocchio?"

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text: "Ever think Pinocchio was mad that Geppetto made him?"

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text: "You think Pinocchio felt lonely being the only wooden boy?"

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: "Totally."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text: "Ha."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: "I don't always feel very real."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: "I'm made of wood!"

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text: "Finally i expose you for what you really are:"

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: "There's just no plausible way I could exist."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: "I'm just an actor in some big play."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text: "Wow."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text: "A hard shell that's easy to break."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text: "Am I part of it?"

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text: "Are you the main character?"

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: "A huge part."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text: "Awesome."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: "Unfortunately yes. No can understand my concerns and it's so much work!"

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text: "That's a shame."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text: "It must be hard memorizing all the lines. You can't just guess because theatre never makes any logical sense. You have to prepare and know their lines ahead of time."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: "Well, over time I'm sure you get the gist of theatre-logic."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text: "And if you don't?"

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: "Then you're a bad actor!"

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text: "Amen."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: "When you knock it's hollow inside."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text: "A fine production of high calibre Italian wood!"

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: "Pretty, but functionally useless."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text: "Can only give warmth if you burn it."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text: "You think there's a conspiracy at play here?"

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: "Oh definitely. So many small contradictions. Shadows of secret spies following my every move."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text: "False promises and lies. Disappointments."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: "Evil agents out to make me different from everyone else. They have a plan for me."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text: "And they will stop at nothing."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: "Damn right."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: "I would be."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text: "Why?"

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: "He could've spent all that energy adopting a real boy."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: "He only made the second best thing."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text: "With real emotions and real friends."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: "A boy that could give and receive real love."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text: "With the real consequences that follow."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: "Shit."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text: "Maybe that anger is what prevented Pinocchio from becoming a real boy?"

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text: "I often feel angry."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: "Nah, it was probably just the disobedience."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text: "It must be weird knowing you we're always meant to be something else."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: "A kind of living consolation price."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text: "A thing you only love half-halfheartedly."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: "Absolutely."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: "Frustrated might be the better word to use though."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: "What do you do when normal advice and the rules of life just doesn't apply to you?"

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text: "Fall into a depressive spiral of doubt and uncertainty."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text: "Relax and give up trying a bunch of things that might be impossible for me to achieve."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: "It would be impossible to really know when you did something wrong."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: "Oops! Look's like I'm incompatible with human relationships!"

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: "For you all you know, your friends might hate you, and your greatest enemies love you."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text: "Why bother trying with these pesky relationships?"

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text: "I'm sorry."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text: "I finally understand."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: "... I exaggerated."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text: "You gave me what I came for: An understanding."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: "All you need to understand is that I was trying to hurt you."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: "An understanding of what?"

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text: "Why everything was like that back then."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text: "Why I'm incapable of making friends."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text: "It's just me. It's not because of you, it's not because of the world, it's just me. I picked a bad straw."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: "That's pessimistic."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: "I'm sure there's other people with similar problems."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text:
"I don't think you're a bad straw."
[D]

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text: "Society is overtly toxic to pessimism. We're addicted to naive hope and sweet agreeable morals."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text: "'Things will get better!', 'You can solve your problems!', 'One day you'll find your group!'"

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text: "If it doesn't neatly fit your reality then you're %pessimistic%."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: "There's a lot more people than you to blame."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text: "There is, huh?"

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text:
"I just want something better for you."
[D]

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: "You really shouldn't think so much about what I told you."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text: "You just feel uncomfortable that life isn't nice for everyone."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text: "So you tell yourself and others lies."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text: "It's okay."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: "Listen ... just ... arghhh."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: "There's this island, right?"

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text: [X]"What?"

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: "There's this island, and people live in peace and harmony, okay?"

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text: [X]"I don't get it."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: "... don't be."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text: "I had misunderstood everything."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: "What do you mean?"

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text: "You %helped me%."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text: "I finally get why everything was like that back then."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text: "I finally get why I'm incapable of making friends."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: [X]"... But that's the way it should be right?"

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text: "It's dark, it's brutal, it doesn't hold back to make us feel better. It dares to show us the truth, even if that truth hurts."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: "Amen."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text: "I'm hurt."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: "What the hell was she thinking telling me this?"

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text: "She was using fantasy to teach you how to deal with reality."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text: "I'm so hurt."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: "And the reality is that people are fucking stupid."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: "Worked out well."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: "Just don't be! Ha!"

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: "I'm so tired."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text: "God, what happened."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text:
"I'm broken,"
[H]The choices

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text:
"I'm broken because you broke me,"
[H]are fucking

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text:
"there is no hope for broken souls like me."
[H]pointless.

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text:
"I'll gladly break you again,"
[H]There is only

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text:
"I'll gladly break you because it's the only thing I know to do,"
[H]one

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text:
"there is no hope for an empty soul like me."
[H]ending.

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text: "I want to have many friends, I want to have fun, I want to party and make memories, I want to use my youth to the fullest. Am i running out of time?"

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text: [X]"Okay ... "

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text: "I want to do all those things I saw you do back then. All those things you're probably doing right now."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text: "For a long time, I so badly wanted people's recognition. I wanted them to like me, and I was angry that they didn't. Eventually i realised I was being selfish: Why should I expect anything if I give nothing in return?"

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text: "But what could I ever hope to give? I can put in hard work and accomplish my goals, but you just can't prepare for personality. Even if you try, you'll always end up being you. It's the luck of the draw, and I didn't get to be funny, or quirky, or easy to talk to."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text: "I can't just say what I want to say, because I always have to guess what a %normal% person would think."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text: "Since I left, I held on tightly to our time back then, but now I see that was stupid. We were incompatible from the start."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: "You we're never the problem, it was always me. I corrupt whatever ecosystem I'm placed into to put myself at some artificial top."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: "The only thing I can give to others is the lie that I'm better. This distracts me until I realize there is absolutely nothing behind it."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: "%I don't know how to do anything%! I'm fucking useless! I don't care about anything!"

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: "I took a gap year to travel alone and find myself. I didn't find shit. Now I'm studying communication."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: "You're passionate about things. You're smart to be more than self-aware. Don't say you forgive me, I don't deserve to be forgiven!"

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: "We were incompatible. I was only showing you kinship and empathy back then to fix myself."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text: [X]"You'll never truly understand how I feel."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: [X]"Neither will you"

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text: [X]"No one can fix my personality for me."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: [X]"No one can help me find mine."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text: [X]"I won't change."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: [X]"I will never change."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Narrator
DialogueFragments.Text: Then finally, the two young women confessed their love.

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Narrator
DialogueFragments.Text: They felt relieved and happy to no longer carry this burden and weight in their hearts.

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Narrator
DialogueFragments.Text: They hugged, they embraced, they told each other to forget about all those things they just said.

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Narrator
DialogueFragments.Text: Moving forwards, they would have tea, do their nails, watch Friends, and go shopping.

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Narrator
DialogueFragments.Text: They would live in a tiny little apartment and tell each other mundane, half-truths like 'I'll miss you' when leaving for work.

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Narrator
DialogueFragments.Text: Together, they would be so very boring.

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Narrator

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Narrator
DialogueFragments.Text: Just this once, her expression contains no multitudes, it is as simple as a child.

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Klara
DialogueFragments.Text: "It's just me. It's not because of you, it's not because of the world, it's just me. I picked a bad straw."

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: They're just acting to please me or their peers. They have no internal will of their own.

DialogueFragments.Speaker: Sofie
DialogueFragments.Text: I'm no different. Just burdened with a pesky, all-consuming self-awareness.
